snippet.textDisplay:
Things coming in the foreseeable future and whether I'm eagerly waiting to see how they perform: Intel bringing out a dedicated laptop GPU? Meh. AMD bringing out Zen 3 and RDNA2 laptop CPUs and GPUs? YES. Nvidia bringing out RTX 3000-series laptop GPUs? YES. Intel bringing out Tiger Lake mobile CPUs? Maybe yes?

Zen 2 on mobile was already so good, and the RTX 3000-series such a step up from the 2000-series, that combining the two (or maybe an RDNA2 GPU?) might seriously make me consider getting a new laptop.  Hopefully there will be reasonable options in the price range of current R5 4600H + RTX 2060 equipped units.
